				Vendor Terms &amp; Conditions			</h1>

<div class="breadcrumbs-wrapper"><nav role="navigation" class="yoast_breadcrumbs content-wrapper" aria-label="Breadcrumb Navigation">
<div aria-label="breadcrumb navigation"><a href="https://www.williams.com/">Home</a> &gt; <span class="breadcrumb_last" aria-current="page" title="You are here">Vendor Terms &amp; Conditions</span></div>

<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="the-williams-companies-inc-terms-conditions"><strong>The Williams Companies, Inc., Terms &amp; Conditions</strong></h2>



<p>The following Williams’ standard terms and conditions shall apply to all Purchase Orders, unless we have entered into a separate written agreement. Please retain a copy for your files, unless otherwise notified to the contrary. These terms and conditions do not take precedence over any existing Williams contract.</p>



<p>All Purchase Orders will be transmitted to you via fax, e-mail, or U.S. mail. The terms and conditions will be provided along with the purchase order.</p>



<p>Williams requires a routing code (code used to direct the internal flow of an invoice received from our suppliers) on all invoices when submitted for payment. Failure to obtain and include the routing code on all invoices will result in the non-payment and return of the invoice to the supplier.</p>



<div class="wp-block-buttons is-layout-flex wp-block-buttons-is-layout-flex">
<div class="wp-block-button is-style-show-more-highlight-button"><a class="wp-block-button__link wp-element-button" href="https://www.williams.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2023/01/Purchase-Order-TsCs-effective-Feb-1-2023.pdf">View Terms and Conditions of Purchase Order effective feb 1, 2023</a></div>
</div>
